From 5fe20e7bdcc473ac6ca5a73aec6aa1b90cee9de8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alejandro Pena <adpena@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 16:50:26 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] codex-core: retire finalized spawned agents to release slot
 ownership

Before:
- AgentRegistry::release_spawned_thread is called only on
  CodexErr::InternalAgentDied (agent/control.rs:693) and on explicit
  shutdown_live_agent (agent/control.rs:714).
- Completed / Errored finalization (mapped from TurnComplete /
  TurnAborted in agent/status.rs) does NOT retire a slot.
- A finalized subagent's session stays alive holding its
  McpConnectionManager and counts against agents.max_threads until
  something else triggers removal.
- V1 multi_agents has a completion watcher gated `!MultiAgentV2` at
  control.rs:307; V2 has no equivalent.

After:
- AgentMetadata.slot_state: SlotState
  (NotTracked / Active / Retired { last_status }), replacing the prior
  slot_active: bool + last_status: Option<AgentStatus>.
- AgentRegistry::retire_spawned_thread(id, status) transitions
  Active -> Retired { .. } and decrements total_count exactly once.
  Idempotent under repeated retire / interleaved release.
- AgentControl::retire_finalized_agent flushes rollout, enqueues
  Op::Shutdown on the session's submission channel (so the session
  loop drains it into handlers::shutdown, picking up #19753's
  begin_shutdown()), removes the live thread, and retires the slot.
  Invoked from V1's maybe_start_completion_watcher and from V2's
  Session::maybe_notify_parent_of_terminal_turn via tokio::spawn
  (synchronous V2 invocation self-deadlocks: the call site runs inside
  Session::send_event and the bounded submission channel's receiver is
  the same loop).
- Retires only Completed / Errored. Shutdown is intentionally not
  retired (broad retirement of Shutdown regresses an existing
  resume-path test).
- get_status / wait_agent / list_agents fall back to cached registry
  status when no live thread exists. resume_agent switches to
  has_live_thread() rather than treating any non-NotFound status as
  proof of non-resumability.
- SpawnReservation::Drop releases the reserved nickname when spawn
  setup fails before commit.

Out of scope:
- Per-session McpConnectionManager ownership (design decision).
- Shutdown participation in retirement (regresses an existing
  resume-path test).
- Live-descendant drain on root shutdown (raced destructively with
  ThreadManager::shutdown_all_threads_bounded; needs cooperation with
  ThreadManager on cleanup authority).

Tests:
- spawn_agent_releases_slot_after_completion (V1)
- v2_spawn_agent_releases_slot_after_completion (V2)
- retire_releases_slot_and_preserves_cached_status
- failed_spawn_releases_reserved_nickname
- retire_after_release_does_not_double_decrement
- retire_is_idempotent_for_repeated_calls
- release_after_retire_does_not_double_decrement

Verification on a fresh openai/codex@80fb0704ee clone with this patch:
